Subject: Narrative Digestion Layer

Description: Layer that turns weightier narrative moments into subject-layer SOP network records.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\ApertureReentryCycle.sop

& [NarrativeDigestionLayer] is the layer for digesting narrative into the SOP subject network
  + [layer_key] is narrative
  + [node_role] is N:narrative:<moment_key>
  + [edge_role] is E:digests:<moment_key>
  + [input] is turns, steps, stages, internal reflection moments, and scan events
  + [weightier_narrative] is narrative with pressure or impact intensity, repeated return, explicit correction, or causal draw
  + [second_pass_narrative] is the follow-up narrative formed from a closed reentry_springboard after aperture survey
  + [subject_declaration_pass] is the SOP pass that names or updates subjects, relations, and boundaries discovered by second_pass_narrative
  + [subject_layer_target] is the appropriate SOP subject layer where the narrative should persist
  + [output] is a subject-layer SOP record, SOP-HG graph, or residual outside note
  + [viewfinder_snapshot] is a structured capture when narrative needs commit-framed comparison, reweighing, and reframing

  = must: digest weightier narrative into durable SOP only when it changes project understanding
  = must: digest second_pass_narrative only after the aperture cycle has closed into a reentry_springboard
  = must: route subject_declaration_pass to subject-layer records without overwriting preserved source or first-pass narrative
  = must: preserve lighter narrative as periphery or scan trace
  = must: keep bookends and evidence paths attached
  = must: use ViewfinderSnapshot when previous reflection must be compared against current observation
  - never: rewrite prior narrative with hindsight
